					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-543209#post-2117886</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-543209/scp-1239#post-2117886</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2014 08:58:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Le_C5</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1277668</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I absolutely love how this SCP is written.<br /> First we get the bit about not seeing the right objects, which by itself is not very threatening. Then we get the fact that children seem always happy whatever happens, which is kinda disquieting, but not by itself too dangerous as long as we don't put people with strange ideas in there. Then the fact that hallucinations fade once the area is left, which is creepy because of the fridge horror element (&quot;why did I keep laughing while the kid was crying ?&quot;), but still not dreadful.<br /> Then we get the list of items, and the description quietly stops as we are left to connect the dots. And the full horror kicks in.</p> <p><sub>Upvoted, in case my gushing was not clear enough</sub></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
