					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-543209#post-1531515</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-543209/scp-1239#post-1531515</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 08 Aug 2012 20:21:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Pig_catapult</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>233556</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>tbh, I upvoted as soon as I saw the picture, and I saw no reason to change it by the time I reached the end.</p> <p>The pyrovision thing didn't even occur to me until I saw it mentioned in the comments, but I think saying that this is &quot;just pyrovision&quot; is selling it short. That seems to me like the same sort of superficial comparison being put forward as that one guy who asked if I based 811 on the Spitter enemy from Left 4 Dead 2, just because they have bloated stomachs and use projectile vomit as a weapon. Yes, it makes things seem so happy and fluffy when they're not, but the end result is much different, and the execution had that &quot;Huh, this is kind of odd. I wonder why they'd need that specifically.&quot; → &quot;Okay, I could see how that could go wrong in the right circumstances&#8230;&quot; → &quot;Oh. <em>Oh.</em> Oh <em>crap.</em>&quot; progression that I love.</p> <p>The biggest thing, though, that I think sets this apart from &quot;just pyrovision&quot;, is that the pyrovision trailer is largely Played For Laughs, and in a setting where violence and death isn't permanent; every character in those games can be respawned infinitely, to the point of it being possible to have multiple simultaneous iterations of the same character, and the characters in question, despite looking like faerie babies in Pyrovision, are in fact all adults. This, on the other hand, is a suckerpunch straight to one of the most visceral parental fears, that you might end up hurting or killing your children without realising it, with the added horror that, afterwards, you will never understand why, leaving you with that gnawing, unabated guilt for the rest of your life.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
